Job Description:
RESPONSIBILITIES:
Kforce's client, a growing and established Engineering Technology company is seeking a New Product Introduction Engineer (NPI). The company offers a competitive compensation package including base salary, an aggressive annual bonus (20%), 401K matching, PTO and benefits.

Summary:
The NPI Engineer designs manufacturing process flows to introduce new products to internal and external lines, supporting product launches. They recommend or manage designs for test equipment, assembly aids, and rework stations for electro-mechanical products throughout development. As part of NPD Scrum Teams from project inception, the Senior NPI Engineer will evaluate product designs for manufacturability and assembly using DFMA best practices.

Responsibilities:
* Lead efforts in defining the manufacturing process flow and manufacturing process control plans for low to mid-volume electro-mechanical products
* Work with Manufacturing Engineers at Contract Manufacturers, Design Engineers, Quality Engineers, and other team members to define the testing and assembly process for new products
* Collaborate with design and quality engineers to develop non-standard, specialty test equipment as required by product design engineering during development
* Collaborate with external Contract Manufacturers to design assembly fixtures that that will be used to assemble low to mid-volume electro-mechanical products
* Contribute to DFMA and FMEA exercises on new product designs and provide feedback to design engineers; Apply DFMA best practices and knowledge of product design, part fabrication, product assembly, tooling, and materials to evaluate the design
* Work as a liaison between NPD Project Teams and Contract Manufacturers to ensure manufacturing lines and fixtures are ready for pilot runs; Solicit feedback from assembly line operators for assembly design improvements
* Perform mechanical tests on new products that are produced from pilot runs as needed

REQUIREMENTS:
* B.S. in Mechanical Engineering, Manufacturing, Mechatronics, Electrical Engineering, Robotics, or a closely related degree required; Master's degree in related field is a plus but not required
* OSHA 10/30 certification is a plus
* At least 3-5 years of experience in Manufacturing Engineering or NPI role for electro-mechanical products
* Experience laying out manufacturing assembly processes and production lines
* Experience in DFMA principles toward the design of electro-mechanical products
* Proven track record of designing low to mid volume electro-mechanical products and/or test equipment for testing these products
* Experience using common tools such as SolidWorks to perform light mechanical design of assembly aids
* Experience project managing pilot runs of new product development in support of new product introduction
* Experience in creating and editing Work Instructions for Assembly Sites; Familiarity with Dozuki is a plus
* Ability to perform light mechanical/electrical assembly for lab, assembly or test equipment
* Experience performing root cause analysis investigations
* Experience working with Assembly Operators
* Proven track record of collaborating with teams to design and develop products from concept to production
* Clear, concise technical writing skills focused on equipment set-up, equipment use procedures and manufacturing process control plans
* Proficient in status reporting, communicating technical data/results and issues, impacts and corrective actions
* Experience writing, reviewing and coordinating Deviations for Production Lines
* Have current passport and the ability to travel to Mexico once a quarter (typically, 2 or 3 days in Mexico)
* Project Management experience is a plus, but not required
* Experience working in an ISO 9001:2015 environment a plus
* Experience in Waterfall and/or Agile NPD processes is a strong plus

What you'll do...
International Recommendations platform is a multi-tenant framework that powers the personalization experiences for Mexico, Canada, and other Walmart International sites. The team drives innovation in Machine Learning to provide personalized results for our customers and drive business KPIs.

As a Staff Software Engineer, you'll spend your days translating requirements into solutions, writing code, collaborating with teams, and providing us with the insights necessary to think beyond the status quo. You'll oversee small project teams consisting of other engineers who will look to you as a trusted advisor, a subject matter expert who provides guidance and the right tools.


Focusing on customer, associate and business needs, this team works with Walmart International, which includes more than 5,200 retail units, operating in 23 countries such as Canada, Central America, Chile, China, India, Mexico and South Africa to name a few.




Imagine working in an environment where one line of code can make life easier for hundreds of millions of people. That's what we do at Walmart Global Tech. We're a team of software engineers, data scientists, cybersecurity expert's and service professionals within the world's leading retailer who make an epic impact and are at the forefront of the next retail disruption. People are why we innovate, and people power our innovations. We are people-led and tech-empowered. We train our team in the skillsets of the future and bring in experts like you to help us grow. We have roles for those chasing their first opportunity as well as those looking for the opportunity that will define their career. Here, you can kickstart a great career in tech, gain new skills and experience for virtually every industry, or leverage your expertise to innovate at scale, impact millions and reimagine the future of retail.


We use a hybrid way of working that is primarily in office coupled with virtual when not onsite. Our campuses serve as a hub to enhance collaboration, bring us together for purpose and deliver on business needs. This approach helps us make quicker decisions, remove location barriers across our global team and be more flexible in our personal lives.


Benefits: Beyond our great compensation package, you can receive incentive awards for your performance. Other great perks include 401(k) match, stock purchase plan, paid maternity and parental leave, PTO, multiple health plans, and much more.

Extraordinary teams building inspiring projects:

Since 1898, we have helped customers complete more than 25,000 projects in 160 countries on all seven continents that have created jobs, grown economies, improved the resiliency of the world's infrastructure, increased access to energy, resources, and vital services, and made the world a safer, cleaner place.

Differentiated by the quality of our people and our relentless drive to deliver the most successful outcomes, we align our capabilities to our customers' objectives to create a lasting positive impact. We serve the Infrastructure; Nuclear, Security & Environmental; Energy; Mining & Metals, and the Manufacturing and Technology markets. Our services span from initial planning and investment, through start-up and operations. Core to Bechtel is our Vision, Values and Commitments. They are what we believe, what customers can expect, and how we deliver. Learn more about our extraordinary teams building inspiring projects in our Impact Report.



Bechtel is partnering with NextDecade to support their vision to provide the world access to lower carbon intensive energy with their Rio Grande LNG (RGLNG) project in Brownsville, Texas. RGLNG is a natural gas liquefaction and export terminal situated on a 984-acre site on the banks of the Brownsville ship channel. The first phase of the RGLNG project consists of three liquefaction trains, two storage tanks and one marine berth. At full capacity, the five-train facility will have a production capacity of 27 million tonnes per annum (MTPA). Brownsville, Texas is a city known for its diverse history, tradition, and rich culture. Located in the southernmost region in the beautiful state of Texas, lays Brownsville a rich, tropical oasis bordering the Rio Grande River and near the shores of the Gulf of Mexico. Brownsville embraces innovation, looks forward to the future and beyond!



In this role, you will provide project field engineering specialization and expertise with work planning and packaging, material management, quantity verification and validation, safety and quality control, technical inspection and testing knowledge, and subcontract coordination. The Boeing Company is currently seeking a Lead Strategic Deterrent Systems Software Engineer-Aerospace Vehicle Equipment (AVE) to support our SDS Software Engineering team located in Layton, Utah.
